                  <handDesc>
                  <handNote xml:id="h1" script="Ethiopic">
                  <seg type="rubrication">
                  <foreign xml:lang="gez">ኢግዚአብሔር፡</foreign>
                  <foreign xml:lang="gez">ማርያም፡</foreign>
                  </seg>
                  <desc>The word God is rubricated in the first three works; the word Mary is rubricated in the final two works. Occasionally, the word God is rubricated in alternating red and black letters (e.g., <locus target="#80v" facs="081">fol. 80v</locus>)</desc>
                  <desc>Columetric layout of text: <locus target="#97v" facs="098">fols. 97v, </locus> (Ps. 145); <locus target="#98v" facs="099">98v, </locus> (Ps. 150); <locus target="#107r #107v" facs="107 108">107r, 107v</locus> (tenth biblical canticle)</desc>
                  </handNote>
                  </handDesc>
                  <decoDesc>
                    <decoNote type="miniature" xml:id="d1"><locus target="#54v" facs="055">Fol. 54v</locus><desc><ref type="authFile" corresp="https://betamasaheft.eu/AT1082Angel">Angel</ref></desc></decoNote>
                    <decoNote type="miniature" xml:id="d2"><locus target="#71r" facs="071">Fol. 71r</locus><desc><ref type="authFile" corresp="https://betamasaheft.eu/AT1082Angel">Angel</ref> with <term key="scabbard" ana="#scabbard"/></desc></decoNote>
                    <decoNote type="miniature" xml:id="d3"><locus target="#85r" facs="085">Fol. 85r</locus><desc> Orante <ref type="authFile" corresp="https://betamasaheft.eu/AT1071Cross">Cross</ref></desc></decoNote>
                    <decoNote type="frame" xml:id="d4">
                    Decorative designs:
                    <locus target="#1r #7r #13r #19r #27r #33r #38r #45r #54v #66v #77v #88r #90v #99r #110v #116r" facs="001 007 013 019 027 033 038 045 055 067 078 088 091 099 111 116">folss. 1r, 7r, 13r, 19r, 27r, 33r, 38r, 45r, 54v, 66v, 77v, 88r, 90v, 99r, 110v, 116r, </locus> (ḥaräg);
                    <locus target="#62r #94v" facs="062 095">62r, 94v, </locus> (alternating red and black dots);
                    <locus target="#123r" facs="123">123r</locus> (multiple full stops)
                    </decoNote>
                  </decoDesc>
                  <additions>
                  <list>
                    <item xml:id="a1">
                    <locus target="#127v" facs="128">Fol. 127v</locus>
                    <desc type="Asmat">
                    Asmat prayer against Wild Animals, in Amharic; see the Gǝ`ǝz, <foreign xml:lang="gez">ጸሎት: በእንተ: መስተሃድር:</foreign>
                    </desc>
                    </item>
                    <item xml:id="e1">
                    <locus target="#50r" facs="050">Fol. 50r</locus>
                    <desc>
                    the midpoint of the Psalms is marked with alternating red and black dots
                    </desc>
                    </item>
                    <item xml:id="e2">
                    <locus target="#63v" facs="064">Fol. 63v</locus>
                    <desc>
                    words of text are written interlinearly
                    </desc>
                    </item>
                    <item xml:id="e3">
                    <locus target="#12v" facs="013">Fol. 12v</locus>
                    <desc>
                    lines of text are written interlinearly
                    </desc>
                    </item>
                    <item xml:id="e4">
                    <locus target="#58v #110r #127r" facs="059 110 127">Fols. 58v, 110r, 127r</locus>
                    <desc>
                    erasure markings are visible
                    </desc>
                    </item>
                    <item xml:id="e5">
                    <locus target="#17r #24r #68v #118r #121r" facs="017 024 118 121">Fols. 17r, 24r, 68v, 118r, 121r</locus>
                    <desc>
                    text has been removed
                    </desc>
                    </item>
                    <item xml:id="e6">
                    <locus target="#23v #24r" facs="024">Fols. 23v, 24r</locus>
                    <desc>
                    This scribe has avoided the problem of lines of text too long to fit on one line by adopting an aspect ratio that leaves ample room for the width of most lines. Occasionally a line is too long and has to be completed above or below the end of the line.
                    </desc>
                    </item>
                  </list>
